<br>
I don't have great gear, but its probably above average for xp groups at least, and I can't tank for toffee in PoP.  (I mean tier 2 here.)  Unslowed, I need to blow stonestance to survive a PoV mob until slow hits.  The only time I ever end up tanking through choice is when the MT has died, and the damage is so streaky its not funny.  Unslowed with 5k hps from buffs, I need chealing at 100 to last til cheal lands on the Geonid mobs.  Once its slowed I can tank a bit, but will need more cheals than a plate class tank, so its not efficient on healer mana.  And I can't hold agro anyway, unless the enchanter holds off slowing or the wizzies put away their nukes until the mob is already low on hps they are going to end up tanking until root lands.<br>
<br>
I used to tank a lot in xp groups before PoP.  I had done so ever seen I started my monk in 1999.  I don't object to Sony introducing zones where I am an inadequate tank, but I did object to them nerfing my ability to take a hit just because JoeUberMonk00 was rampage tanking in VT.  Mainly because it resulted in me dying on pulls a lot more, and not just on raids.<br>
<br>
I can't see why Warriors are jealous of monks being able to tank like (or better than) rangers when they have been able since the inception of the game.  We still don't approach the tanking abilities of warriors, who have 2k more hps and far more AC. <br>
<br>
As for soloing, its a moot point, I can't solo anything dark blue anymore, the moment I dinged 61, I lost that forever.  /mourn Velks<br>
<br>
I can see that Warrior agro is a serious issue and that xp groups are choosing Paladins and SKs in preference.  <br>
I (and most monks I imagine) would support any change to improve warrior taunt, even the extent of adding some kind of guaranteed hate effect to warrior taunt.  I don't see why this would be broken, given that even chaining tash/slow/cripple/weakness straight off the bat with my Enchanter and then sitting down, I still don't get agro off a Pally friend who tanks in xp groups with me regularly.  If I cast just slow and sit with a warrior tank, the mob is on me in a second.<br>
<br>
